==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Micropyle
<hw>Mi"cro*pyle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ gate, orifice: cf. F. <ets>micropyle</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An opening in the membranes
surrounding the ovum, by which nutrition is assisted and the entrance of
the spermatozoa permitted.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An opening in the
outer coat of a seed, through which the fecundating pollen enters the
ovule.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Mi*crop"y*lar</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microscopal</ent>⟦br⟧
